[3] USA - North Carolina
Date: 20 Feb 2020
Source: The News & Observer [edited]
https://www.newsobserver.com/news/state/north-carolina/article240481031.html


Eleven flu-related deaths, including one child, were reported in North Carolina last week, health officials announced Thursday [20 Feb 2020].

The 11 deaths were reported during the week of 9-15 Feb 2020, bringing the state total to 90 flu-related deaths since the season began in late September 2019, according to the N.C. Department of Health and Human Services.

Three children have died of flu-related illnesses in the state this season [2019-2020], officials say. The death of a child between the ages of 5 and 17 was reported last week.

Two weeks ago, a child under the age of 5 died, The News & Observer reported.

The majority of deaths in the state have been among those ages 65 and older, the health department says.

By this time last year [2019], 58 flu-related deaths had been reported in the state, according to health officials. A total of 203 deaths were reported last season [2018-2019].

There were 1146 positive cases of the virus reported in the state last week, bringing the total to more than 8300 cases since the season started, the health department says.

Last flu season [2018-2019], the state had more than 9200 positive cases of the virus.

Nationally, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention have reported 92 pediatric flu-related deaths this season [2019-2020].

