******
[4] USA - Oklahoma
Date: 20 Feb 2020
Source: Kfor TV [edited]
https://kfor.com/news/local/flu-deaths-continue-to-rise-in-oklahoma/


Officials with the Oklahoma State Department of Health announced this week that 240 Oklahoma patients had been hospitalized with the flu, bringing the total number of hospitalizations to 1970 since 1 Sep 2019.

Also, health experts say the death toll associated with the virus rose, bringing the total number of deaths in Oklahoma to 36 since the flu season began in September 2019.

Official data indicate that one patient was younger than 5 years old, another was between 5 years old and 17 years old, while 6 were between the ages of 18 and 49 years old. The other 28 patients were over the age of 50 years old.

Health officials said the flu claimed the lives of 85 Oklahomans last flu season [2018-19] and led to more than 2891 hospitalizations statewide. Last flu season was the longest flu season in a decade, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.

